"{\"uid\": \"aljazeera.com-features-2024-7-27-why-the-olympic-surfing-venue-is-16000km-away-from-paris\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Teahupo'o on the island of Tahiti in the territory of French Polynesia is home to 'the heaviest', 'most perfect' waves in the world.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 132, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 27, \"end\": 33, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.313662984946516e-13, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 61, \"end\": 70, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.057814823169857e-16, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 9}, {\"ngram\": \"the island\", \"from\": 13, \"to\": 23}, {\"ngram\": \"the territory\", \"from\": 37, \"to\": 50}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 74, \"to\": 78}, {\"ngram\": \", 'most perfect' waves\", \"from\": 96, \"to\": 118}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 122, \"to\": 131}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But what's it got to do with Paris?\", \"from\": 133, \"to\": 168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 162, \"end\": 167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.908381575892769e-26, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Save Share Waves are formed when ocean swells, stirred by far off storms, make contact with the seafloor.\", \"from\": 170, \"to\": 277, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Save Share Waves\", \"from\": 170, \"to\": 186}, {\"ngram\": \"ocean swells\", \"from\": 203, \"to\": 215}, {\"ngram\": \"storms\", \"from\": 236, \"to\": 242}, {\"ngram\": \"contact\", \"from\": 249, \"to\": 256}, {\"ngram\": \"the seafloor\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 274}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Typically, this is a gradual process, but at Teahupo'o, Tahiti, site of the 2024 Paris Olympics surfing event, every parameter is taken to its extreme.\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 334, \"end\": 340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.313662984946516e-13, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a gradual process\", \"from\": 297, \"to\": 314}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 350, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"surfing event\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 387}, {\"ngram\": \"every parameter\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 404}, {\"ngram\": \"its extreme\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 428}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The monster waves' swells originate from powerful Antarctic storms before traversing thousands of kilometres of open ocean and crashing into a coral reef less than a metre (less than yard) deep.\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 625, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The monster waves' swells\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 456}, {\"ngram\": \"powerful Antarctic storms\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 497}, {\"ngram\": \"thousands\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 525}, {\"ngram\": \"kilometres\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 539}, {\"ngram\": \"open ocean\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 553}, {\"ngram\": \"a coral reef\", \"from\": 572, \"to\": 584}, {\"ngram\": \"a metre\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 602}, {\"ngram\": \"yard\", \"from\": 614, \"to\": 618}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The result is a perfect tube of eye-watering intensity that can be navigated only by the very best surfers in the world.\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 746, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The result\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 636}, {\"ngram\": \"a perfect tube\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 654}, {\"ngram\": \"eye-watering intensity\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 680}, {\"ngram\": \"the very best surfers\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 732}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 745}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As surf coach and author Jason Bortewrites: \\\"Guts alone may cut it at some big-wave venues, but here they will get you killed.\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 873, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 772, \"end\": 777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"score\": 0.9999998356115747, \"rank\": 1.6438700398565583e-07, \"text\": \"Jason\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Guts\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 796}, {\"ngram\": \"some big-wave venues\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 837}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An iron sack must be accompanied by finesse in negotiating a wave that has relegated Pipeline [Hawaii's heaviest wave] to mere warm-up status.\\\"\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 1017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 969, \"end\": 975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"score\": 0.9999999940810085, \"rank\": 5.919083514328043e-09, \"text\": \"Hawaii\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An iron sack\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 886}, {\"ngram\": \"finesse\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 917}, {\"ngram\": \"a wave\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 939}, {\"ngram\": \"Pipeline\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 967}, {\"ngram\": \"mere warm-up status\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1015}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Teahupo'o, which means \\\"heap of heads\\\" in Tahitian, is also painfully picturesque, says Tim McKenna, a veteran surf photographer who has lived on the island since 2002.\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1187, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1061, \"end\": 1069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5833238882258081e-38, \"text\": \"Tahitian\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1028}, {\"ngram\": \"heap\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1047}, {\"ngram\": \"heads\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1056}, {\"ngram\": \"Tim McKenna\", \"from\": 1107, \"to\": 1118}, {\"ngram\": \"a veteran surf photographer\", \"from\": 1120, \"to\": 1147}, {\"ngram\": \"the island\", \"from\": 1165, \"to\": 1175}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McKenna has spent the past 35 years photographing the world's best surfers on the world's best waves but, he says, \\\"There is nowhere else like Teahupo'o.\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1341, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"McKenna\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1195}, {\"ngram\": \"the past 35 years\", \"from\": 1206, \"to\": 1223}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's best surfers\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1262}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's best waves\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1288}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2026 The water is warm and super clear.\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1378, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The water\", \"from\": 1344, \"to\": 1353}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can see the coral and the fish.\\\"\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1415, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the coral\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1400}, {\"ngram\": \"the fish\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1413}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The surrounding scenery is equally impressive: \\\"When you catch the wave, you are surfing towards these super-green, pyramid-shaped mountains.\\\"\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1559, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The surrounding scenery\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1440}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1488}, {\"ngram\": \"these super-green, pyramid-shaped mountains\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1557}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But what truly sets the wave apart, he adds, is that \\\"it's super short, super powerful and 100 percent tube.\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1668, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1588}, {\"ngram\": \"super short, super powerful and 100 percent tube\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1667}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's why it's so photogenic.\", \"from\": 1669, \"to\": 1699, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2026 When the guys come out the tube, you will get the spray in your face and on your lens.\\\"\", \"from\": 1700, \"to\": 1789, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the guys\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1715}, {\"ngram\": \"the tube\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1733}, {\"ngram\": \"the spray\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1757}, {\"ngram\": \"your face\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1770}, {\"ngram\": \"your lens\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1787}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is because there is a channel right next to the wave that's \\\"so deep there is no way anything can happen to you.\", \"from\": 1790, \"to\": 1907, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a channel\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 1824}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 1839, \"to\": 1847}, {\"ngram\": \"no way\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1879}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even if the waves are massive, the channel is flat.\\\"\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1960, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the waves\", \"from\": 1916, \"to\": 1925}, {\"ngram\": \"the channel\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 1950}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is, he repeats, \\\"nowhere else like Teahupo'o in the world\\\".\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 2026, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2015, \"to\": 2024}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet that's not the only reason why this village of 1,455 people in southwest Tahiti has been chosen to host 48 of the world's top surfers for the Paris Olympics starting on Saturday, 16,000km (10,000 miles) away from the capital of France.\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2105, \"end\": 2111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.313662984946516e-13, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 2260, \"end\": 2266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999947749529, \"rank\": 5.222958919397227e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the only reason\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2058}, {\"ngram\": \"this village\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2075}, {\"ngram\": \"1,455 people\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2091}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's top surfers\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2165}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2188}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 2201, \"to\": 2209}, {\"ngram\": \"16,000km\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2219}, {\"ngram\": \"10,000 miles\", \"from\": 2221, \"to\": 2233}, {\"ngram\": \"the capital\", \"from\": 2245, \"to\": 2256}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The short answer: French Polynesia is part of France, and it's home to the best waves in the world.\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2294, \"end\": 2303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.057814823169857e-16, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 2315, \"end\": 2321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999947749529, \"rank\": 5.222958919397227e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2311}, {\"ngram\": \"the best waves\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2354}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2358, \"to\": 2367}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The long answer is more interesting.\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2405, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The long answer\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2384}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mainland France is home to some fantastic winter waves - most notably,La Graviere and Le Nord near Hossegor- but in summer, the Bay of Biscay on the west coast is largely waveless.\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2407, \"end\": 2422, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metropolitan_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mainland France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metropolitan_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metropolitan_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2542, \"end\": 2548, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bay_of_Biscay\", \"score\": 0.9999999976189429, \"rank\": 2.3812766022108325e-09, \"text\": \"Biscay\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bay_of_Biscay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bay_of_Biscay\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some fantastic winter waves\", \"from\": 2434, \"to\": 2461}, {\"ngram\": \"summer\", \"from\": 2523, \"to\": 2529}, {\"ngram\": \"the Bay\", \"from\": 2531, \"to\": 2538}, {\"ngram\": \"the west coast\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2566}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surfing made its debut at the Tokyo Olympics in fairly dismal conditions, and a repeat would not be good for the sport's image.\", \"from\": 2588, \"to\": 2715, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its debut\", \"from\": 2601, \"to\": 2610}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 2614, \"to\": 2632}, {\"ngram\": \"fairly dismal conditions\", \"from\": 2636, \"to\": 2660}, {\"ngram\": \"a repeat\", \"from\": 2666, \"to\": 2674}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport's image\", \"from\": 2697, \"to\": 2714}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Luckily for the Olympic organisers, France's overseas territories boast some brilliant waves.\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2752, \"end\": 2758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999947749529, \"rank\": 5.222958919397227e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic organisers\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2750}, {\"ngram\": \"some brilliant waves\", \"from\": 2788, \"to\": 2808}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The best Olympic wave would probably have been Saint-Leu on the island of Reunion,\\\" McKenna says, because it requires surfers to be able to ride barrels and perform manoeuvres.\", \"from\": 2811, \"to\": 2988, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2859, \"end\": 2868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Leu,_R\\u00e9union\", \"score\": 0.8679271843055405, \"rank\": 0.12548262548263228, \"text\": \"Saint-Leu\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Leu,_R\\u00e9union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint-Leu,_R\\u00e9union\"}, {\"begin\": 2886, \"end\": 2893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reunion_Records\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8374322420258144e-29, \"text\": \"Reunion\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reunion_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reunion_Records\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The best Olympic wave\", \"from\": 2812, \"to\": 2833}, {\"ngram\": \"the island\", \"from\": 2872, \"to\": 2882}, {\"ngram\": \"McKenna\", \"from\": 2896, \"to\": 2903}, {\"ngram\": \"surfers\", \"from\": 2930, \"to\": 2937}, {\"ngram\": \"barrels\", \"from\": 2957, \"to\": 2964}, {\"ngram\": \"manoeuvres\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 2987}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the very real possibility of a shark attack - Reunion, east of Madagascar in the Indian Ocean, recorded 24 attacks, 11 of them fatal, from 2011 to 2019 - meant Teahupo'o was the better option.\", \"from\": 2989, \"to\": 3185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3056, \"end\": 3066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madagascar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.033105238960237e-15, \"text\": \"Madagascar\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madagascar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madagascar\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the very real possibility\", \"from\": 2993, \"to\": 3018}, {\"ngram\": \"a shark attack - Reunion\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3046}, {\"ngram\": \"east\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3052}, {\"ngram\": \"the Indian Ocean\", \"from\": 3070, \"to\": 3086}, {\"ngram\": \"24 attacks\", \"from\": 3097, \"to\": 3107}, {\"ngram\": \"the better option\", \"from\": 3167, \"to\": 3184}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is also a homecoming of sorts for the sport itself.\", \"from\": 3187, \"to\": 3241, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a homecoming\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3210}, {\"ngram\": \"sorts\", \"from\": 3214, \"to\": 3219}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 3224, \"to\": 3233}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surfing was invented by the ancient Polynesians, who later took the pastime to Hawaii, well before the first European contact in the 16th century.\", \"from\": 3243, \"to\": 3389, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3279, \"end\": 3290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.965719261161154, \"rank\": 0.03546367613928606, \"text\": \"Polynesians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 3322, \"end\": 3328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"score\": 0.9999999940810085, \"rank\": 5.919083514328043e-09, \"text\": \"Hawaii\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the pastime\", \"from\": 3307, \"to\": 3318}, {\"ngram\": \"the first European contact\", \"from\": 3342, \"to\": 3368}, {\"ngram\": \"the 16th century\", \"from\": 3372, \"to\": 3388}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During Captain James Cook's three-month stay in Tahiti in 1769, Joseph Banks, the resident botanist on HMS Endeavour, noted in his journal: \\\"Their chief amusement was carried on by the stern of an old canoe, with this before them they swam out as far as the outermost breach, then one or two would get into it and opposing the blunt end to the breaking wave were hurried in with incredible swiftness.\", \"from\": 3390, \"to\": 3790, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3397, \"end\": 3415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cook\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.007665696204517e-79, \"text\": \"Captain James Cook\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cook\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cook\"}, {\"begin\": 3405, \"end\": 3415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cook\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2037846075763605e-55, \"text\": \"James Cook\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cook\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cook\"}, {\"begin\": 3438, \"end\": 3444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.313662984946516e-13, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 3454, \"end\": 3466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joseph_Banks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1890768796741425e-69, \"text\": \"Joseph Banks\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joseph_Banks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joseph_Banks\"}, {\"begin\": 3493, \"end\": 3506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HMS_Endeavour\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"HMS Endeavour\", \"types\": [\"Q11446\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HMS_Endeavour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HMS_Endeavour\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the resident botanist\", \"from\": 3468, \"to\": 3489}, {\"ngram\": \"his journal\", \"from\": 3517, \"to\": 3528}, {\"ngram\": \"Their chief amusement\", \"from\": 3531, \"to\": 3552}, {\"ngram\": \"the stern\", \"from\": 3571, \"to\": 3580}, {\"ngram\": \"an old canoe\", \"from\": 3584, \"to\": 3596}, {\"ngram\": \"the outermost breach\", \"from\": 3644, \"to\": 3664}, {\"ngram\": \"the blunt end\", \"from\": 3713, \"to\": 3726}, {\"ngram\": \"the breaking wave\", \"from\": 3730, \"to\": 3747}, {\"ngram\": \"incredible swiftness\", \"from\": 3769, \"to\": 3789}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes they were carried almost ashore.\\\"\", \"from\": 3791, \"to\": 3834, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While Polynesia is the birthplace of surfing, trying to tame the death-defying tubes of Teahupo'o is a more recent endeavour.\", \"from\": 3838, \"to\": 3963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3844, \"end\": 3853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.057814823169857e-16, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the birthplace\", \"from\": 3857, \"to\": 3871}, {\"ngram\": \"surfing\", \"from\": 3875, \"to\": 3882}, {\"ngram\": \"the death-defying tubes\", \"from\": 3899, \"to\": 3922}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 3926, \"to\": 3935}, {\"ngram\": \"a more recent endeavour\", \"from\": 3939, \"to\": 3962}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It seems the first people to surf big Teahupo'o were Hawaiian bodyboarders Mike Stewart and Ben Severson in 1986 with the waves becoming \\\"something of an underground spot for psychotic bodyboarders\\\", according to Borte.\", \"from\": 3964, \"to\": 4183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4017, \"end\": 4025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"score\": 0.999998466378468, \"rank\": 1.532182047874941e-06, \"text\": \"Hawaiian\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\"}, {\"begin\": 4039, \"end\": 4051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Stewart_(bodyboarder)\", \"score\": 0.5748271395638268, \"rank\": 0.5724852071004936, \"text\": \"Mike Stewart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Stewart_(bodyboarder)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Stewart_(bodyboarder)\"}, {\"begin\": 4056, \"end\": 4068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Severson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ben Severson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Severson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Severson\"}, {\"begin\": 4177, \"end\": 4182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/B\\u00f6rte\", \"score\": 0.9851762361960458, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Borte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/B\\u00f6rte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/B\\u00f6rte\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first people\", \"from\": 3973, \"to\": 3989}, {\"ngram\": \"big Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 3998, \"to\": 4011}, {\"ngram\": \"the waves\", \"from\": 4082, \"to\": 4091}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 4102, \"to\": 4111}, {\"ngram\": \"an underground spot\", \"from\": 4115, \"to\": 4134}, {\"ngram\": \"psychotic bodyboarders\", \"from\": 4139, \"to\": 4161}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Bodyboarders, who do not have to get to their feet to ride waves, often pioneer big wave \\\"slabs\\\", which are intense and powerful waves created by very deep water crashing onto shallow rock or coral.)\", \"from\": 4184, \"to\": 4384, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"(Bodyboarders\", \"from\": 4184, \"to\": 4197}, {\"ngram\": \"their feet\", \"from\": 4225, \"to\": 4235}, {\"ngram\": \"waves\", \"from\": 4244, \"to\": 4249}, {\"ngram\": \"big wave \\\"slabs\", \"from\": 4265, \"to\": 4280}, {\"ngram\": \"intense and powerful waves\", \"from\": 4293, \"to\": 4319}, {\"ngram\": \"very deep water\", \"from\": 4331, \"to\": 4346}, {\"ngram\": \"shallow rock\", \"from\": 4361, \"to\": 4373}, {\"ngram\": \"coral\", \"from\": 4377, \"to\": 4382}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the 1990s, a few gung-ho surfers had followed suit, but it was the decision to host a World Surf League (WSL) event there in 1997 that threatened to put Teahupo'o on the map.\", \"from\": 4385, \"to\": 4562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4474, \"end\": 4497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Surf League (WSL)\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Surf_League\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1990s\", \"from\": 4388, \"to\": 4397}, {\"ngram\": \"a few gung-ho surfers\", \"from\": 4399, \"to\": 4420}, {\"ngram\": \"suit\", \"from\": 4434, \"to\": 4438}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 4451, \"to\": 4463}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 4541, \"to\": 4550}, {\"ngram\": \"the map\", \"from\": 4554, \"to\": 4561}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That first event, McKenna remembers, was an unmitigated disaster.\", \"from\": 4564, \"to\": 4629, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That first event\", \"from\": 4564, \"to\": 4580}, {\"ngram\": \"McKenna remembers\", \"from\": 4582, \"to\": 4599}, {\"ngram\": \"an unmitigated disaster\", \"from\": 4605, \"to\": 4628}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The waves did not get bigger than 3-4ft [0.9 to 1.2 metres].\", \"from\": 4630, \"to\": 4691, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The waves\", \"from\": 4631, \"to\": 4640}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The wind turned onshore, and a ferry ended up getting stuck on the reef.\\\"\", \"from\": 4692, \"to\": 4765, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The wind\", \"from\": 4692, \"to\": 4700}, {\"ngram\": \"a ferry\", \"from\": 4721, \"to\": 4728}, {\"ngram\": \"the reef\", \"from\": 4755, \"to\": 4763}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fortunately, he adds, the organisers \\\"held strong and ran the contest again the next year and the waves were amazing\\\".\", \"from\": 4766, \"to\": 4884, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the organisers\", \"from\": 4788, \"to\": 4802}, {\"ngram\": \"the contest\", \"from\": 4824, \"to\": 4835}, {\"ngram\": \"the waves\", \"from\": 4860, \"to\": 4869}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the 2000 competition, the waves were even bigger: \\\"We got up the next morning, and it was like nothing I'd ever seen in my life,\\\" event organiser Steve Robertson remembers.\", \"from\": 4886, \"to\": 5062, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5036, \"end\": 5051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Robertson_(racing_driver)\", \"score\": 0.9999970343031558, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steve Robertson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Robertson_(racing_driver)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Robertson_(racing_driver)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2000 competition\", \"from\": 4890, \"to\": 4910}, {\"ngram\": \"the waves\", \"from\": 4912, \"to\": 4921}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 4985, \"to\": 4992}, {\"ngram\": \"my life\", \"from\": 5010, \"to\": 5017}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was easily 12ft [3.7 metres], but it wasn't the size that worried us.\", \"from\": 5063, \"to\": 5136, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the size\", \"from\": 5111, \"to\": 5119}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 5133, \"to\": 5135}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sheer power was unbelievable and completely uncharted territory for an event.\", \"from\": 5137, \"to\": 5218, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The sheer power\", \"from\": 5137, \"to\": 5152}, {\"ngram\": \"unbelievable and completely uncharted territory\", \"from\": 5157, \"to\": 5204}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 5209, \"to\": 5217}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We thought, 'Can we really run and make these guys go out in this surf?'\", \"from\": 5219, \"to\": 5291, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these guys\", \"from\": 5259, \"to\": 5269}, {\"ngram\": \"this surf\", \"from\": 5280, \"to\": 5289}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We had a really good field of surfers, and it was just too perfect to call it off.\", \"from\": 5292, \"to\": 5374, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a really good field\", \"from\": 5299, \"to\": 5318}, {\"ngram\": \"surfers\", \"from\": 5322, \"to\": 5329}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We knew we could do it.\", \"from\": 5375, \"to\": 5398, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So we did.\\\"\", \"from\": 5399, \"to\": 5410, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That event was won by Kelly Slater - the first of five Teahupo'o titles for a man universally acknowledged as the GOAT of surfing.\", \"from\": 5411, \"to\": 5541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5433, \"end\": 5445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Slater\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kelly Slater\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Slater\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelly_Slater\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That event\", \"from\": 5411, \"to\": 5421}, {\"ngram\": \"five Teahupo'o titles\", \"from\": 5461, \"to\": 5482}, {\"ngram\": \"a man\", \"from\": 5487, \"to\": 5492}, {\"ngram\": \"the GOAT\", \"from\": 5521, \"to\": 5529}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the 2000 contest played a major role in etching Teahupo'o at the pinnacle of surfing's totem pole, it was another moment in that same year that changed the sport of surfing forever.\", \"from\": 5543, \"to\": 5730, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2000 contest\", \"from\": 5549, \"to\": 5565}, {\"ngram\": \"a major role\", \"from\": 5573, \"to\": 5585}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 5597, \"to\": 5606}, {\"ngram\": \"the pinnacle\", \"from\": 5610, \"to\": 5622}, {\"ngram\": \"surfing's totem pole\", \"from\": 5626, \"to\": 5646}, {\"ngram\": \"another moment\", \"from\": 5655, \"to\": 5669}, {\"ngram\": \"that same year\", \"from\": 5673, \"to\": 5687}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 5701, \"to\": 5710}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At 11:38am on August 17, 2000, American big wave surfer Laird Hamilton was towed into a wave using a Jet Ski.\", \"from\": 5731, \"to\": 5840, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"11:38am\", \"from\": 5734, \"to\": 5741}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 5745, \"to\": 5751}, {\"ngram\": \"a wave\", \"from\": 5817, \"to\": 5823}, {\"ngram\": \"a Jet Ski\", \"from\": 5830, \"to\": 5839}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Above a certain size, it becomes impossible to paddle fast enough to catch a wave.)\", \"from\": 5841, \"to\": 5925, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a certain size\", \"from\": 5848, \"to\": 5862}, {\"ngram\": \"a wave\", \"from\": 5917, \"to\": 5923}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Matt Warshaw, the pre-eminent historian of surfing, described the feat as \\\"the single heaviest thing I have ever seen in surfing.\\\"\", \"from\": 5926, \"to\": 6056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5926, \"end\": 5938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Warshaw\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matt Warshaw\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Warshaw\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Warshaw\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the pre-eminent historian\", \"from\": 5940, \"to\": 5965}, {\"ngram\": \"surfing\", \"from\": 5969, \"to\": 5976}, {\"ngram\": \"the feat\", \"from\": 5988, \"to\": 5996}, {\"ngram\": \"the single heaviest thing\", \"from\": 6001, \"to\": 6026}, {\"ngram\": \"surfing\", \"from\": 6047, \"to\": 6054}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McKenna,who shot the fold-out cover image for Surfer magazine, explains: \\\"Before then people only measured big wave surfing by the size of the wave.\", \"from\": 6058, \"to\": 6206, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6104, \"end\": 6119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfer_(magazine)\", \"score\": 0.9999999674537327, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Surfer magazine\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfer_(magazine)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfer_(magazine)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"McKenna\", \"from\": 6058, \"to\": 6065}, {\"ngram\": \"the fold-out cover image\", \"from\": 6075, \"to\": 6099}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 6144, \"to\": 6150}, {\"ngram\": \"the size\", \"from\": 6185, \"to\": 6193}, {\"ngram\": \"the wave\", \"from\": 6197, \"to\": 6205}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Compared to open ocean waves, that wave was not that big, \\u2026 but it was so round and so gnarly and so perfect.\", \"from\": 6207, \"to\": 6316, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ocean waves\", \"from\": 6224, \"to\": 6235}, {\"ngram\": \"that wave\", \"from\": 6237, \"to\": 6246}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It opened up a whole new world of big wave surfing on slabs that previously only bodyboarders could access.\", \"from\": 6317, \"to\": 6424, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a whole new world\", \"from\": 6330, \"to\": 6347}, {\"ngram\": \"slabs\", \"from\": 6371, \"to\": 6376}, {\"ngram\": \"only bodyboarders\", \"from\": 6393, \"to\": 6410}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It redefined what was possible.\\\"\", \"from\": 6425, \"to\": 6457, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The wave may have been ridden only recently, but it's been there hundreds of thousands of years - long before humans arrived on the island.\", \"from\": 6459, \"to\": 6598, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The wave\", \"from\": 6459, \"to\": 6467}, {\"ngram\": \"hundreds of thousands\", \"from\": 6524, \"to\": 6545}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 6549, \"to\": 6554}, {\"ngram\": \"humans\", \"from\": 6569, \"to\": 6575}, {\"ngram\": \"the island\", \"from\": 6587, \"to\": 6597}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French were not the first European power to try to exert control over the hearts and minds of Tahitians.\", \"from\": 6600, \"to\": 6708, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6604, \"end\": 6610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9998474281143143, \"rank\": 0.00015257284452841583, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 6698, \"end\": 6707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahitians\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6255380104053872e-51, \"text\": \"Tahitians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahitians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahitians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first European power\", \"from\": 6620, \"to\": 6644}, {\"ngram\": \"control\", \"from\": 6661, \"to\": 6668}, {\"ngram\": \"the hearts\", \"from\": 6674, \"to\": 6684}, {\"ngram\": \"minds\", \"from\": 6689, \"to\": 6694}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Spanish and the British both tried, but from 1842 until the present day, the area has been under some form of French control.\", \"from\": 6709, \"to\": 6838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6713, \"end\": 6720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_Empire\", \"score\": 0.638249277495047, \"rank\": 0.4337879983036603, \"text\": \"Spanish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spanish_Empire\"}, {\"begin\": 6729, \"end\": 6736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.978339307035045, \"rank\": 0.021729414454320344, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 6823, \"end\": 6829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.9998474281143143, \"rank\": 0.00015257284452841583, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the present day\", \"from\": 6769, \"to\": 6784}, {\"ngram\": \"the area\", \"from\": 6786, \"to\": 6794}, {\"ngram\": \"some form\", \"from\": 6810, \"to\": 6819}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We vote in Tahitian elections, French elections and European elections,\\\" McKenna says with a laugh.\", \"from\": 6839, \"to\": 6939, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6851, \"end\": 6859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5833238882258081e-38, \"text\": \"Tahitian\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"McKenna\", \"from\": 6913, \"to\": 6920}, {\"ngram\": \"a laugh\", \"from\": 6931, \"to\": 6938}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the 2000s and 2010s, the independence movement - championed by Oscar Temaru, leader of the Tavini Huiraatira (Serving the Indigenous People) party - enjoyed considerable support.\", \"from\": 6941, \"to\": 7122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7007, \"end\": 7019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Temaru\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Oscar Temaru\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Temaru\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oscar_Temaru\"}, {\"begin\": 7035, \"end\": 7052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tavini_Huiraatira\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tavini Huiraatira\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tavini_Huiraatira\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tavini_Huiraatira\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2000s\", \"from\": 6944, \"to\": 6953}, {\"ngram\": \"2010s\", \"from\": 6958, \"to\": 6963}, {\"ngram\": \"the independence movement\", \"from\": 6965, \"to\": 6990}, {\"ngram\": \"leader\", \"from\": 7021, \"to\": 7027}, {\"ngram\": \"the Indigenous People\", \"from\": 7062, \"to\": 7083}, {\"ngram\": \"considerable support\", \"from\": 7101, \"to\": 7121}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Temaru won French Polynesia's 2023 elections and his fifth term as president in a landslide, the situation is calmer (in stark contrast to nearby New Caledonia) these days, McKenna says.\", \"from\": 7123, \"to\": 7315, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7147, \"end\": 7156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.057814823169857e-16, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 7275, \"end\": 7288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Caledonia\", \"score\": 